Modular restructure of DO3SE model
==================================

+   Inputs_mod.f90
    -   All input variables
    -   All procedures required for loading input data

+   Params_Veg_mod.f90
    -   Cover type/species related parameters
    -   Any extra procedures for loading/setting these parameters

+   Params_Site_mod.f90
    -   All site-specific parameters (elevation, soil properties, etc.)
    -   Any extra procedures for loading/setting these parameters

+   Variables_mod.f90
    -   Variables which do not belong to any one particular module

+   Functions_mod.f90
    -   Procedures with generic uses (for example polygons for growing season)

+   R_mod.f90
    -   Calculations for all resistances that must be derived (Ra, Rb, Rsur, 
        Rinc, Rsto, rb)
    -   Resistances supplied as parameters can be found in their respective
        modules (e.g. Rsoil is in Params_Site_mod.f90)

+   Rsto_mod.f90
    -   Interchangeable module for Rsto/Gsto calculations

+   Phenology_mod.f90
    -   Calculations resulting in fphen - growing season, SAI, etc.

+   Environmental_mod.f90
    -   Calculations relating to the environment the vegetation exists within
        (ftemp, fVPD, uses Soil_mod for fSWP, uses Irradiance_mod for flight)

+   Soil_mod.f90
    -   Calculations for soil properties, mainly SMD and SWP

+   Irradiance_mod.f90
    -   Calculations deriving the components of the solar radiation, 
        plus the flight calculation

+   O3_Flux_mod.f90
    -   Calculations for the O3 flux data (Ftot, Fns, Fstom, Fst, AFstY, AOT40)

+   Yield_Loss_mod.f90
    -   Calculation for yield loss

All public variables are static (using the `save` keyword) to facilitate use
between modules.

Dependancies look something like this:

+   Yield_Loss_mod
    +   O3_Flux_mod
        +   R_mod
            +   Rsto_mod
                +   Phenology_mod
                +   Environmental_mod
                    +   Soil_mod
                        +   Evapotranspiration_mod
                    +   Irradiance_mod
                +   Soil_mod
                    +   Evapotranspiration_mod

Pretty much all modules rely on parts from Params_Veg_mod, Params_Site_mod, 
Inputs_mod, Variables_mod and Functions_mod.  Some also rely on each other, 
these dependancies will be solved with static variables and careful ordering
of the calls to procedures.
